      "role": "user",
      "content": "i was just thinking about the math of everything. like, if you look at the scale of the universe and the sheer randomness of existing, the probability of any single human life having actual objective value is basically zero. it feels like we're just accidental noise in a system that doesn't care. it's hard to find a reason to keep going when the math just says nothing matters.",
